column5: This is a bear that I see very often at a lake in the central Ontario area, thought you guys would like to see it ! Has anyone seen anything like this before ? She is a fat gal too !!!
good name for her. She looks like a wise old soul.
There is one at the temagami dump that has a belly that drags on the ground
Well feed sow Thanks for sharing Leechman
Ya, she looks like she has been around for awhile , I will try too find some more pictures of her.
I have heard of Bears with that colour referred to as a "Cinnamon Bear"
That is a great shot of that boar. Looks like he is the king around that part of the woods.
